types of transformation - 
1. narrow transformation = transformation doesn't inculdes multiple partitions while execution -- so no shuffle data b/w partition hence this are faster
        eg - map(), filter(), select()

2. wide transformation = transformation does inculdes multiple partitions while execution
        eg - groupby(), joins, coalesce, repartition 

